    "abstract": "In this paper, we study the sub-critical dissipative quasi-geostrophic equations (S\u03b1). We prove that there exists a unique local-in-time solution for any large initial data \u03b80 in the space \u03c71-2\u03b1(R2) defined by (1). Moreover, we show that (S\u03b1) has a global solution in time if the norms of the initial data in \u03c71-2\u03b1(R2) are bounded by 1/4. Also, we prove a blow-up criterion of the local-in-time solution of (S\u03b1).",
